373
00:27:04,300 --> 00:27:06,400
Thank you!

374
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:11,200
Miao Miao's mom, aren't you dieting? I made some without sugar for you.

375
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,800
Here.

376
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,100
Thank you.

377
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:16,600
You really are considerate.

378
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:20,000
Look at this. The bear cookies really are quite adorable.

379
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,600
- This is probably Yuwei's father, right? 
 - Yeah.

380
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:24,800
- First time meeting. 
 - Hi, everyone. 
 - Hello.

381
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:26,600
Hello.

382
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:30,000
Miao Miao's mother, he also went to SJTU.

383
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:32,800
He and Miao Miao's grandmother are schoolmates.

384
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:39,400
I'm from the class of '04. What about her?

385
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:42,100
My mother went to Cornell.

386
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:48,200
I remembered incorrectly.

387
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:51,100
But I guess my grandfather could be considered a part of SJTU.

388
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,800
May I ask? What was his major?

389
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:58,600
He wasn't a student. He was one of the board of directors of the school.

390
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:00,300
That's so admirable.

391
00:28:00,300 --> 00:28:02,800
You don't even know what my grandfather's name was.

392
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:05,000
What would you be admiring?

393
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:12,080
Before we were talking about decorating the place,

394
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,900
I can't manage it myself.

395
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:16,000
- The party? 
 - Yeah.

396
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,000
What place are you guys decorating?

397
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:22,300
- Next month, we want to host an "I Love Mom" party.
 - That's great.

398
00:28:22,300 --> 00:28:25,800
We want to make the party a bit fashionable, but we don't have enough people.

399
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,500
- I can help! 
 - Really? 
 - Yes.

400
00:28:28,500 --> 00:28:32,400
- That would be great— 
 - We should talk about it a little more.

401
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,400
We'll meet up again then.

402
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:37,800
Sounds good.

403
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:40,200
We'll discuss it later.

404
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:43,740
The children are out!

405
00:28:44,300 --> 00:28:46,000
They're out.

406
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:48,900
 Where's Miao Miao? 

407
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:03,100
 [@Everyone, lets have a meeting tomorrow afternoon to discussion the party preparations, don't be late!] 

408
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:05,200
Miao Miao's mom added me as a friend again.

409
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:07,800
She also added me into the elite group chat.

410
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:11,600
She says that tomorrow night we're going to have a meeting to talk about the party preparations.

411
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:14,000
Is there a need to be so excited?

412
00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:22,000
- She took full responsibility and used her own insurance? 
 - Yes.

413
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:25,300
- How is that okay? 
 - How is it not?

414
00:29:25,300 --> 00:29:28,400
You already promised her before that you would take full responsibility,

415
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,700
